Fix code-web.sh to work when node is available on PATH

Adds a check for the node command and runs the web server directly
instead of going through the code() wrapper function, fixing startup
in environments where node is globally available.

Index: code-editor-src/scripts/code-web.sh
===================================================================
--- code-editor-src.orig/scripts/code-web.sh
+++ code-editor-src/scripts/code-web.sh
@@ -24,4 +24,9 @@ function code() {
 	$NODE ./scripts/code-web.js "$@"
 }
 
-code "$@"
+if command -v node &> /dev/null; then
+	cd $ROOT
+	node ./scripts/code-web.js "$@"
+else
+	code "$@"
+fi
